From: ceblair@ux1.cso.uiuc.edu (Charles Blair)
Subject: Re: SLS considered harmful (wasRe: Bashing Peter MacDonald)
Date: 28 Aug 1993 16:44:28 GMT

  I'm a very happy MCC user who has never tried SLS.  I get the clear impression
that SLS has given high priority to having as many features available as poss-
ible, while MCC has concentrated on a smaller number with more documentation
and debugging.

   There is clearly a place for both systems, but I think those who recommend
SLS to newcomers are misguided.   There was a time when MCC didn't have as
many things available as it does now (no emacs, for example) and a more 
difficult installation procedure, and I think many of those who recommend SLS
have not seen the new MCC.

   No big deal, but I think the installation process for the recent versions
of MCC borrowed (with acknowledgement) some ideas from SLS.

