hi 2u2,

 > Hi.  Zyxel modems were mentioned several times as a good modem
                                                       ^^^^
                                                       simply the best
Features:

- 14'400 bps (V32bis, V42bis)
- up to 16'800 bps + 19'200 bsp proprietery
- Fax up to 14'400 bps
- Voice (your pc turnes into a phone-answring machine)
- two years warranty and free firmware upgrade (new features etc.)

 > to use
 > for high speed connections using Linux.
                              ^^^^^^^^^^^
I don't think the modem REALLY cares about the operating system (but it cares about it's abilities for flow-control, i.e. the OS should be able to provide Hardware (CTS/RTS) flow control. This is true for ANY high-speed modem
 > I have never seen these advertised.  Anyone know any mail order
 > vendors
 > of these modems?

I suppose you're sitting in the USA. Unfortunately ZyXEL's ain't very well known in the US (probably US-people prefer US-products, ZyXEL is taiwanese). Here in Europe (especially Germany and Switzerland, where I am sitting) they have an overwelming success: 18 month back you hardly found any BBS using a ZyXEL - now you hardly find a BBS that doesn't have at least 1 line with a ZyXEL with it's 19'200 bps support :-))

Unfortunately there is no SW included for UNIX (Linux) only for DOS, but seyon works fine, GNU-Fax should work, but I didn't try and if you want to use the voice-option (see above), you will have to write something yourself (at least as far as I know) (if you do: please post it, so I can also use it ;-))

Hope the following helps:

