From: jhenders@jonh.wimsey.bc.ca (John Henders)
Subject: Re: High speed modems & Linux
Date: Sun, 29 Aug 1993 19:42:27 GMT

heiser@bumetb.bu.edu (Bill Heiser) writes:

>Have you done anything to customize your uucp configuration?  The
>best rate I've seen here so far is about 1100CPS, but on average it
>is much worse.

    I get good transfer rates without having done anything special. I
have a cheap serial i/o card, but it has a 16550 on it. My gettydefs
line has CRTSCTS in it, but I think that only matters on incoming calls.
    If you're having problems with retries and dropped characters, maybe
flow control it not turned on. Try setserial. If your modem has mnp5
turned on, turn it off. 
    It could be because my feed also uses Taylor uucp, so they negotiate
a faster protocal, but I don't know because the logs don't record that.


-- 
John Henders       GO/MU/E d* -p+ c+++ l++ t- m--- s/++ g+ w+++ -x+

